    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>Originally exclusive to military operators, a laser designator can focus a precise, invisible beam on a target, helping others to pinpoint it in their sights. Only creatures with darkvision or who can see the infrared spectrum (using @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.equipment.Item.EU79dfSf8xdsAnNT]{infrared sensors}, @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.equipment.Item.CW8QWIhaO5cwWIvs]{darkvision capacitors}, or something similar) can detect this beam. As a full action, you can attempt to aim the laser designator at a target within 1,000 feet by making a ranged attack roll against that target’s EAC – 5. Until the start of your next turn, allies who can see the laser gain a +1 circumstance bonus to attack rolls against that target.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.effects.Item.CbC114QwTObgm9Cj]{Effect: Laser Designated}</p>"
